00:00:15.974 --> 00:00:18.268 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM]
Ninety-eight points?

00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:23.481 position:50% align:center
That's so close to perfect.

00:00:23.565 --> 00:00:27.318 position:50% align:center
[chuckles] Then can
I go play for a while?

00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:28.403 position:50% align:center
Explain.

00:00:28.486 --> 00:00:29.821 position:50% align:center
[ZEN gasps]

00:00:31.156 --> 00:00:33.950 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM] How did you
miss those two points?

00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:37.829 position:50% align:center
[ZEN grunts]
I'm really sorry.

00:00:42.542 --> 00:00:44.878 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM]
That doesn't answer my question.

00:00:44.961 --> 00:00:47.797 position:50% align:center
Why those mistakes
in particular?

00:00:51.176 --> 00:00:53.845 position:50% align:center
Can you tell me?

00:00:55.722 --> 00:00:56.431 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
Hey!

00:00:56.514 --> 00:00:57.849 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM grunts]

00:00:57.932 --> 00:01:01.186 position:50% align:center
Hurry up! We're gonna be
late to the birthday party!

00:01:01.269 --> 00:01:03.730 position:50% align:center
There's a birthday party?

00:01:05.815 --> 00:01:08.318 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM] Why is this the
first I'm hearing about it?

00:01:08.401 --> 00:01:11.071 position:50% align:center
Have you been hiding
things from your own mother?

00:01:11.154 --> 00:01:12.989 position:50% align:center
I-I wasn't hiding it!

00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:16.493 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM]
How can a child be so cruel?

00:01:16.576 --> 00:01:18.411 position:50% align:center
Please, let me go, Mom.

00:01:18.495 --> 00:01:20.789 position:50% align:center
I got him a present
with my allowance.

00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:23.083 position:50% align:center
I promise I'll do
better next time!

00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:25.835 position:50% align:center
You promise?

00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:27.128 position:50% align:center
Okay, then.

00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:29.673 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:31.841 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:35.136 --> 00:01:37.806 position:50% align:center
Go on and follow
your father's example.

00:01:37.889 --> 00:01:42.185 position:50% align:center
Betray my trust and walk
out the door, like he did.

00:01:42.268 --> 00:01:44.938 position:50% align:center
Have fun at your friend's party.

00:01:46.856 --> 00:01:50.193 position:50% align:center
[ZEN gasping]

00:01:58.493 --> 00:02:04.082 position:50% align:center
[ZEN grunting]

00:02:08.003 --> 00:02:09.713 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:12.465 position:50% align:center
[CAT 11A meows]

00:02:18.054 --> 00:02:19.889 position:50% align:center
[CAT 11A meows]

00:02:22.767 --> 00:02:24.477 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Hey, Teach?

00:02:24.561 --> 00:02:25.562 position:50% align:center
Mister Zen!

00:02:25.645 --> 00:02:27.188 position:50% align:center
I finished the passage.

00:02:27.272 --> 00:02:28.898 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Hm?

00:02:28.982 --> 00:02:32.068 position:50% align:center
O-Okay. Next reader, please.

00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:33.778 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 11A] He literally
just stopped trying!

00:02:33.862 --> 00:02:35.280 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 11B]
It's not cute anymore.

00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:36.865 position:50% align:center
"He tore her
clothes from her body

00:02:36.948 --> 00:02:38.491 position:50% align:center
and kicked her roughly
down on the corpses

00:02:38.575 --> 00:02:40.827 position:50% align:center
as she struggled, and
tried to clutch his leg.

00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:43.204 position:50% align:center
Five steps, and he was
at the top of the stairs.

00:02:43.288 --> 00:02:44.706 position:50% align:center
The yellow clothes
he had wrested off

00:02:44.789 --> 00:02:46.833 position:50% align:center
were under his arm,
and in a twinkling he had rushed

00:02:46.916 --> 00:02:49.085 position:50% align:center
down the steep stairs
into the abyss of night.

00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.795 position:50% align:center
The thunder of
his descending steps

00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:54.215 position:50% align:center
pounded in the hollow tower,
and then it was quiet."

00:04:30.645 --> 00:04:33.606 position:50% align:center
Aw, jeez. Metabolism's at a ten!

00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:36.151 position:50% align:center
You wanna hit up Mrs. D's
with me real quick?

00:04:36.234 --> 00:04:38.528 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I have plans today.

00:04:38.611 --> 00:04:40.280 position:50% align:center
With your boyfriend?

00:04:40.363 --> 00:04:41.614 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you got me.

00:04:41.698 --> 00:04:43.158 position:50% align:center
That's perfect!

00:04:43.241 --> 00:04:46.369 position:50% align:center
I'll just call my boyfriend and
ask him to meet me for donuts!

00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:47.454 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Sorry.

00:04:47.537 --> 00:04:49.330 position:50% align:center
[HANA]
Mm-mm. See ya!

00:04:49.414 --> 00:04:50.915 position:50% align:center
[MIKO chuckles]

00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:54.252 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:04:57.422 --> 00:04:59.841 position:50% align:center
See ya in the morning,
Mister Zen!

00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:03.261 position:50% align:center
You notice he's always,
like, the first to leave?

00:05:03.345 --> 00:05:05.722 position:50% align:center
And you know what? Good for him.

00:05:14.773 --> 00:05:16.358 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:05:30.955 --> 00:05:32.040 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:32.123 --> 00:05:35.210 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER CATS yowl]

00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:38.713 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] There are more of them
every day, just like I thought.

00:05:38.797 --> 00:05:41.675 position:50% align:center
It's starting to affect Hana.

00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.843 position:50% align:center
[YULIA]
Oh, right, the new substitute.

00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:45.553 position:50% align:center
Being around him
and those spirits

00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:47.514 position:50% align:center
would be a drain on
anybody's life aura,

00:05:47.597 --> 00:05:51.267 position:50% align:center
so I wonder if he might
actually be the problem here.

00:05:51.351 --> 00:05:53.144 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER CATS yowling]

00:05:53.228 --> 00:05:56.398 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I'm scared, really scared.

00:05:56.481 --> 00:05:58.733 position:50% align:center
But I can't just ignore this.

00:05:58.817 --> 00:06:02.153 position:50% align:center
Hana is not going
to suffer on my watch.

00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:06.282 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:08.159 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:14.749 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM (MONSTER)]

00:06:20.296 --> 00:06:22.841 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] If I acknowledge it,
it'll come after me.

00:06:22.924 --> 00:06:25.135 position:50% align:center
On the other hand,
those things might show up

00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:28.471 position:50% align:center
and intervene
for the third time.

00:06:28.555 --> 00:06:30.306 position:50% align:center
That said, if they
could protect me

00:06:30.390 --> 00:06:33.018 position:50% align:center
from all the
monsters swarming him,

00:06:33.101 --> 00:06:36.187 position:50% align:center
they wouldn't be much help if
something worse showed up later.

00:06:36.271 --> 00:06:39.399 position:50% align:center
I'm going to have
to handle this myself.

00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.111 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] If I want to
get him away from Hana,

00:06:43.194 --> 00:06:45.363 position:50% align:center
I need to find proof.

00:06:53.496 --> 00:06:55.165 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Just make
sure it doesn't spot you

00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:57.459 position:50% align:center
while you play stalker.

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:06.217 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] If you see him doing
anything shady, call the police.

00:07:10.055 --> 00:07:11.931 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
He makes one false move,

00:07:12.015 --> 00:07:14.517 position:50% align:center
the school will
kick him to the curb.

00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:22.275 position:50% align:center
[BUSINESS MONSTER 11A moans]

00:07:22.359 --> 00:07:24.944 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
All I can do is see them, sure.

00:07:25.028 --> 00:07:27.530 position:50% align:center
But I'm the only
one who can help.

00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:29.407 position:50% align:center
That's how it is.

00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:40.210 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
He's sticking to places

00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:42.545 position:50% align:center
where there aren't
many people around.

00:07:56.351 --> 00:07:57.727 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:21.960 position:50% align:center
[CAT 11B squeaks]

00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:24.337 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.220 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:37.934 --> 00:08:39.811 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:42.480 position:50% align:center
Stop it!

00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:47.652 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:08:47.736 --> 00:08:49.529 position:50% align:center
Not this guy.

00:08:49.612 --> 00:08:52.782 position:50% align:center
No, I refuse.

00:08:52.866 --> 00:08:55.744 position:50% align:center
Oh, I remember you.

00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:57.537 position:50% align:center
[MIKO whimpers]

00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:59.080 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:08:59.164 --> 00:09:02.917 position:50% align:center
You were that girl who
wouldn't give me the cat.

00:09:03.001 --> 00:09:06.963 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A snarling]

00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:08.089 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:09:08.173 --> 00:09:10.925 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A]
Don't look at him!

00:09:11.009 --> 00:09:13.595 position:50% align:center
[whimpers]

00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:16.139 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A growls]

00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.558 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:23.313 --> 00:09:25.231 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
What are you doing out here?

00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:26.900 position:50% align:center
Ah! I was just--

00:09:26.983 --> 00:09:29.819 position:50% align:center
You followed me, didn't you?

00:09:29.903 --> 00:09:32.030 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:09:32.113 --> 00:09:36.117 position:50% align:center
If you don't mind,
may I please have the cat?

00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:37.952 position:50% align:center
[MIKO whimpers]

00:09:42.207 --> 00:09:44.084 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:09:46.670 --> 00:09:50.507 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Crap, crap, crap, crap!
What the hell am I doing?

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:53.677 position:50% align:center
Why didn't I just stay
hidden and call the cops?

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.888 position:50% align:center
They'd have caught
him red handed!

00:09:56.971 --> 00:10:00.266 position:50% align:center
He'd have been banned
from school in a heartbeat!

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:02.727 position:50% align:center
But I just couldn't
just let him do it!

00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:06.898 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:10:11.403 --> 00:10:13.905 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasping]

00:10:13.988 --> 00:10:15.990 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:22.580 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:10:27.085 --> 00:10:28.253 position:50% align:center
Now, then.

00:10:28.336 --> 00:10:30.922 position:50% align:center
I'd like you to answer
my questions, please.

00:10:33.216 --> 00:10:34.801 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:10:36.469 --> 00:10:38.179 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A groans]

00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:41.516 position:50% align:center
You don't seem to
like me being near cats.

00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:43.852 position:50% align:center
Could you explain that?

00:10:44.728 --> 00:10:46.354 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:46.438 --> 00:10:48.356 position:50% align:center
There's no way.

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:49.441 position:50% align:center
Did you...?

00:10:49.524 --> 00:10:51.818 position:50% align:center
--[MIKO whimpers]
--[CAT 11B yowls]

00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:52.652 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:53.987 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
No!

00:10:54.070 --> 00:10:54.863 position:50% align:center
[ZEN gasps]

00:10:54.946 --> 00:10:56.823 position:50% align:center
[car rumbles]

00:11:03.455 --> 00:11:05.790 position:50% align:center
[thud]

00:11:11.338 --> 00:11:13.214 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:30.440 position:50% align:center
[CAT 11A meowing]

00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:33.360 position:50% align:center
That's not food.
Get out of here.

00:11:35.528 --> 00:11:38.114 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:11:38.198 --> 00:11:39.449 position:50% align:center
[ZEN grunts]

00:11:39.532 --> 00:11:41.034 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:12:08.103 --> 00:12:09.270 position:50% align:center
So, Zen.

00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:11.981 position:50% align:center
Was anything out
of the ordinary today?

00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:16.528 position:50% align:center
No, nothing.

00:12:16.611 --> 00:12:18.363 position:50% align:center
I see.

00:12:21.116 --> 00:12:22.909 position:50% align:center
[ZEN grunts]

00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:29.541 position:50% align:center
Hey, let's play outside!

00:12:29.624 --> 00:12:31.960 position:50% align:center
Thanks, but I can't today.

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:41.261 position:50% align:center
[ZEN chuckles]

00:12:41.344 --> 00:12:43.972 position:50% align:center
--[door clicks]
--[ZEN gasps]

00:12:51.688 --> 00:12:52.981 position:50% align:center
Welcome home.

00:12:53.064 --> 00:12:54.607 position:50% align:center
Why are you out here?

00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:57.485 position:50% align:center
I just came out to get
some fresh air for a second.

00:12:57.569 --> 00:12:59.529 position:50% align:center
I think you've had plenty.

00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:01.740 position:50% align:center
Now go finish your homework.

00:13:01.823 --> 00:13:03.241 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Okay.

00:13:08.997 --> 00:13:10.707 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
I'm home.

00:13:12.584 --> 00:13:14.711 position:50% align:center
Is anyone here?

00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:19.299 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:13:24.054 --> 00:13:26.264 position:50% align:center
[ZEN gasps]

00:13:26.348 --> 00:13:27.974 position:50% align:center
The vermin is gone.

00:13:28.058 --> 00:13:29.976 position:50% align:center
[ZEN gasps]

00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:33.313 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM] Again my son
was hiding something from me,

00:13:33.396 --> 00:13:35.315 position:50% align:center
breaking my heart.

00:13:35.398 --> 00:13:37.817 position:50% align:center
Betrayal after betrayal,

00:13:37.901 --> 00:13:41.821 position:50% align:center
despite my loving you more
than anything in this world.

00:13:41.905 --> 00:13:44.866 position:50% align:center
The only thing I want
is for you to love me back--

00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:47.786 position:50% align:center
to listen to your mother.

00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:51.498 position:50% align:center
Can't you do that, Zen?

00:13:51.581 --> 00:13:54.542 position:50% align:center
[ZEN whimpers]

00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:05.387 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50% align:center
You're not at fault for this.

00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.057 position:50% align:center
But still...

00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:11.434 position:50% align:center
I jumped out in front of a car.

00:14:11.518 --> 00:14:13.853 position:50% align:center
I made my choice.

00:14:15.605 --> 00:14:17.774 position:50% align:center
Was the cat okay, at least?

00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:19.192 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:14:19.275 --> 00:14:21.820 position:50% align:center
My family's planning on
taking care of him for a while.

00:14:21.903 --> 00:14:23.863 position:50% align:center
[meows]

00:14:23.947 --> 00:14:26.408 position:50% align:center
[KYOUSUKE]
What do cats like? Beef bowls?

00:14:26.491 --> 00:14:28.201 position:50% align:center
He's too little to have meat.

00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:29.327 position:50% align:center
Ooh, chocolate?

00:14:29.411 --> 00:14:31.162 position:50% align:center
I don't think so.

00:14:31.246 --> 00:14:32.872 position:50% align:center
Is that right?

00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:34.082 position:50% align:center
I'm glad to hear it.

00:14:34.165 --> 00:14:36.459 position:50% align:center
Uh... I feel awful.

00:14:36.543 --> 00:14:38.294 position:50% align:center
I wanted to keep
the cat away from you

00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:40.380 position:50% align:center
because I thought
you would hurt it.

00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:43.633 position:50% align:center
Seriously? Why is that?

00:14:43.717 --> 00:14:45.218 position:50% align:center
It's hard to explain.

00:14:45.301 --> 00:14:46.720 position:50% align:center
Uhh...

00:14:46.803 --> 00:14:51.016 position:50% align:center
[WINDOW MONSTER 09A growls]
Don't look at him!

00:14:52.017 --> 00:14:54.811 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Without mentioning that.

00:14:54.894 --> 00:14:58.398 position:50% align:center
Sorry. But anyway,
what were you doing?

00:14:58.481 --> 00:15:00.150 position:50% align:center
Patrolling the neighborhood.

00:15:00.233 --> 00:15:03.153 position:50% align:center
We've had someone
abusing cats recently.

00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:06.156 position:50% align:center
I was beginning to
think you were the culprit.

00:15:06.239 --> 00:15:07.699 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:15:07.782 --> 00:15:10.744 position:50% align:center
I got suspicious when I thought
you were tailing me before.

00:15:10.827 --> 00:15:13.121 position:50% align:center
Then I remembered
we met previously.

00:15:13.204 --> 00:15:14.831 position:50% align:center
Your behavior was pretty odd.

00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:17.709 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Yeah, it's... complicated.

00:15:17.792 --> 00:15:19.210 position:50% align:center
And honestly,

00:15:19.294 --> 00:15:22.047 position:50% align:center
you act like a real weirdo
at school sometimes.

00:15:22.130 --> 00:15:24.507 position:50% align:center
That was rude, my bad.

00:15:24.591 --> 00:15:28.219 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Woof. He's not
even wrong, though.

00:15:28.303 --> 00:15:29.763 position:50% align:center
That means

00:15:29.846 --> 00:15:33.183 position:50% align:center
you were creeping around the
back alleys hunting this guy?

00:15:33.266 --> 00:15:35.977 position:50% align:center
Well, that was
the idea, at least.

00:15:36.061 --> 00:15:37.687 position:50% align:center
Hasn't helped yet.

00:15:37.771 --> 00:15:40.899 position:50% align:center
At best, I show up in
time to see them die.

00:15:42.192 --> 00:15:44.903 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I think I understand now.

00:15:44.986 --> 00:15:49.032 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER CATS groan]

00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:52.118 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I guess they stayed with you.

00:15:53.495 --> 00:15:55.830 position:50% align:center
When you need somebody
to take in a stray,

00:15:55.914 --> 00:15:57.916 position:50% align:center
don't turn to social media.

00:15:57.999 --> 00:15:59.292 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:15:59.376 --> 00:16:02.420 position:50% align:center
That's the very first place
these sickos go to look.

00:16:02.504 --> 00:16:04.422 position:50% align:center
You need somebody you can trust.

00:16:04.506 --> 00:16:05.548 position:50% align:center
So, if you find
another cat, be--

00:16:05.632 --> 00:16:08.343 position:50% align:center
[SATORU] Call up
a trusted veterinarian.

00:16:08.426 --> 00:16:09.803 position:50% align:center
'Cause what's one more stray cat

00:16:09.886 --> 00:16:13.807 position:50% align:center
on top of the god-knows-how-many
they've got, right?

00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:15.183 position:50% align:center
Hey, Satoru.

00:16:15.266 --> 00:16:16.976 position:50% align:center
[MIKO grunts]

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:18.395 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
Hm.

00:16:22.774 --> 00:16:23.942 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
It's a bit of a shock

00:16:24.025 --> 00:16:26.569 position:50% align:center
Zen had a student
visit him in the hospital.

00:16:26.653 --> 00:16:29.489 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] I, uh, guess you've known
each other for a while, huh?

00:16:29.572 --> 00:16:32.575 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we've been buddies
since grade school.

00:16:32.659 --> 00:16:35.662 position:50% align:center
I'm a little surprised to
hear that he has any buddies.

00:16:35.745 --> 00:16:38.790 position:50% align:center
You didn't dress
that up at all, did you?

00:16:38.873 --> 00:16:40.250 position:50% align:center
Though, yeah,

00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:42.919 position:50% align:center
he doesn't tend to engage
with people terribly often.

00:16:43.003 --> 00:16:45.213 position:50% align:center
I imagine he hasn't
learned anyone's names.

00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.632 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Nope, not one.

00:16:47.716 --> 00:16:50.468 position:50% align:center
But throwing himself in
front of a car to save a cat?

00:16:50.552 --> 00:16:52.721 position:50% align:center
That definitely sounds like Zen.

00:16:52.804 --> 00:16:54.097 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
For real?

00:16:54.180 --> 00:16:56.057 position:50% align:center
He texted me the other day.

00:16:56.141 --> 00:16:57.392 position:50% align:center
He wanted to let me know

00:16:57.475 --> 00:17:01.354 position:50% align:center
that the cat he'd rescued had
just given birth.

00:17:01.438 --> 00:17:04.482 position:50% align:center
[KITTEN 11A mewling]

00:17:04.566 --> 00:17:08.445 position:50% align:center
[SATORU gasps, grunts]

00:17:09.446 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
He's the one who finds them,

00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:12.824 position:50% align:center
but they all end
up in my clinic.

00:17:12.907 --> 00:17:14.784 position:50% align:center
Why doesn't he
keep one for himself?

00:17:14.868 --> 00:17:17.245 position:50% align:center
It seems like he
really does love them.

00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:20.206 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
Hmm.

00:17:20.290 --> 00:17:23.710 position:50% align:center
Zen's late mother was
a bit of a teapot tyrant.

00:17:23.793 --> 00:17:27.630 position:50% align:center
One day she found a cat he'd
been keeping out in their shed.

00:17:27.714 --> 00:17:30.175 position:50% align:center
He told me it died because
of something he'd done,

00:17:30.258 --> 00:17:33.303 position:50% align:center
but I'm pretty sure
his mom killed it.

00:17:33.386 --> 00:17:34.554 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:34.637 --> 00:17:37.390 position:50% align:center
I was always scared of
her when we were kids.

00:17:37.474 --> 00:17:41.436 position:50% align:center
She was insanely strict in
this creepy, possessive way.

00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:43.730 position:50% align:center
She was always saying,
"Stay away from him!"

00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:44.981 position:50% align:center
"Don't look at him!"

00:17:45.065 --> 00:17:47.442 position:50% align:center
Like he wasn't allowed
to have friends.

00:17:47.525 --> 00:17:50.528 position:50% align:center
Don't look at him!

00:17:50.612 --> 00:17:53.990 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
No, is that thing...?

00:17:54.074 --> 00:17:55.784 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
The woman passed on.

00:17:55.867 --> 00:17:59.162 position:50% align:center
Can't say the same for the
baggage she left him with.

00:18:00.163 --> 00:18:01.915 position:50% align:center
I think that's why he does it.

00:18:01.998 --> 00:18:05.377 position:50% align:center
Rescuing cats might be his
way of trying to move on.

00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:09.297 position:50% align:center
Not sure it's working if
he pulls this kinda crap.

00:18:09.381 --> 00:18:12.008 position:50% align:center
At this point, what
else can I do for him

00:18:12.092 --> 00:18:14.177 position:50% align:center
except take care of
the ones he brings in

00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:16.638 position:50% align:center
till I can find
them forever homes?

00:18:16.721 --> 00:18:19.766 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Why go this far?

00:18:19.849 --> 00:18:22.227 position:50% align:center
Because Zen is my friend,
and he needs help.

00:18:22.310 --> 00:18:24.479 position:50% align:center
It's as simple as that.

00:18:24.562 --> 00:18:26.231 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:26.314 --> 00:18:29.693 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:18:31.653 --> 00:18:34.072 position:50% align:center
[inaudible]

00:18:38.118 --> 00:18:39.244 position:50% align:center
Still,

00:18:39.327 --> 00:18:41.746 position:50% align:center
it does make me feel better,
seeing you here.

00:18:41.830 --> 00:18:43.248 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Huh?

00:18:43.331 --> 00:18:45.375 position:50% align:center
If nothing else, I know
he's at least managed

00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:47.502 position:50% align:center
to make a connection
with his students.

00:18:47.585 --> 00:18:50.171 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Maybe not so much.

00:18:50.255 --> 00:18:53.258 position:50% align:center
I'm glad taking care of cats
helps him deal with the guilt,

00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:57.053 position:50% align:center
but I'd rather see him
do it 'cause he loves cats.

00:18:57.137 --> 00:18:59.139 position:50% align:center
I'm not just saying
that as a vet.

00:18:59.222 --> 00:19:01.433 position:50% align:center
I'm saying it as his friend.

00:19:04.769 --> 00:19:05.937 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
But, hey,

00:19:06.021 --> 00:19:07.772 position:50% align:center
do me a favor and don't
tell him I said that.

00:19:07.856 --> 00:19:10.108 position:50% align:center
It's kind of embarrassing.

00:19:10.191 --> 00:19:12.986 position:50% align:center
[MIKO chuckles]
Got it.

00:19:14.195 --> 00:19:17.032 position:50% align:center
[SATORU sighs] Well,
I have a clinic to get back to.

00:19:17.115 --> 00:19:19.117 position:50% align:center
Try and take it easy, all right?

00:19:21.077 --> 00:19:22.746 position:50% align:center
Hey, wait a sec!

00:19:23.788 --> 00:19:24.831 position:50% align:center
[SATORU]
Hm?

00:19:25.915 --> 00:19:28.168 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Thank you for everything.

00:19:28.251 --> 00:19:30.128 position:50% align:center
[SATORU chuckles]

00:19:48.229 --> 00:19:49.272 position:50% align:center
[door sliding]

00:19:49.356 --> 00:19:52.484 position:50% align:center
[ZEN]
Hm.

00:19:52.567 --> 00:19:54.235 position:50% align:center
Where's Satoru?

00:19:54.319 --> 00:19:56.529 position:50% align:center
He asked me to say bye for him.

00:19:56.613 --> 00:19:59.449 position:50% align:center
He told me that he
needed to get back to work.

00:19:59.532 --> 00:20:01.117 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:20:01.201 --> 00:20:02.744 position:50% align:center
He's who I would have gone to.

00:20:02.827 --> 00:20:05.288 position:50% align:center
When I need to find
a home for a stray cat,

00:20:05.372 --> 00:20:08.083 position:50% align:center
I know I can trust Satoru
to get them somewhere safe.

00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:09.125 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Mr. Toono?

00:20:09.209 --> 00:20:10.251 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:20:10.335 --> 00:20:11.753 position:50% align:center
Once you're feeling better,

00:20:11.836 --> 00:20:14.798 position:50% align:center
do you think you could adopt
the cat you saved today?

00:20:14.881 --> 00:20:16.591 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:20:16.675 --> 00:20:19.427 position:50% align:center
No, bad idea.

00:20:22.347 --> 00:20:25.892 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM]
Don't look at him!

00:20:26.935 --> 00:20:28.687 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I made a snap judgement.

00:20:28.770 --> 00:20:32.107 position:50% align:center
I didn't think,
and someone got hurt.

00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:34.067 position:50% align:center
[inhales]

00:20:34.150 --> 00:20:37.070 position:50% align:center
You really love cats, don't you?

00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:38.613 position:50% align:center
What?

00:20:38.697 --> 00:20:41.199 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM]
Get away!

00:20:44.703 --> 00:20:47.580 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't say I love cats.

00:20:47.664 --> 00:20:49.874 position:50% align:center
That's not what it is.

00:20:49.958 --> 00:20:51.292 position:50% align:center
I think you do.

00:20:51.376 --> 00:20:54.421 position:50% align:center
You jumped in front
of a car to protect one.

00:20:54.504 --> 00:20:55.755 position:50% align:center
That's love.

00:20:55.839 --> 00:20:58.675 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM shrieks]
Don't look at him!

00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:00.885 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM snarling]

00:21:00.969 --> 00:21:05.682 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER CATS yowl]

00:21:07.183 --> 00:21:09.978 position:50% align:center
And that should be enough.

00:21:15.442 --> 00:21:18.987 position:50% align:center
Please, you have
to set him free.

00:21:26.036 --> 00:21:28.496 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM roars]

00:21:29.497 --> 00:21:34.127 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM snarls]

00:21:37.672 --> 00:21:42.344 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM groaning]

00:21:46.431 --> 00:21:49.392 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM groans]

00:21:52.479 --> 00:21:54.356 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:21:54.439 --> 00:21:58.985 position:50% align:center
[ZEN'S MOM groans]

00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:04.949 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
All right, number three...

00:23:35.665 --> 00:23:37.834 position:50% align:center
[JUNJI] Boy, even I wasn't
ready for that last bit!

00:23:37.917 --> 00:23:39.711 position:50% align:center
They just kept piling on the
tension.

00:23:39.794 --> 00:23:42.172 position:50% align:center
Then, boom! At the end
all hell broke loose!

00:23:42.255 --> 00:23:44.174 position:50% align:center
That's what I call
a satisfying slow burn!

00:23:44.257 --> 00:23:45.550 position:50% align:center
Next time, episode 12:

00:23:45.633 --> 00:23:47.802 position:50% align:center
"Mieruko- <i>chan</i> :
The Girl Who Sees"!

00:23:47.886 --> 00:23:49.846 position:50% align:center
No use pretending
anymore, folks!